I"Ç	<blockquote>
  <p>Hashes have a default value that is returned
when accessing keys that do not exist in the hash. If no default is set
nil is used. You can set the default value by sending it as an argument
to Hash.new:</p>

  <p>grades = Hash.new(0)</p>

  <p>Or by using the #default= method:</p>

  <p>grades = {â€œTimmy Doeâ€ =&gt; 8}
 grades.default = 0</p>

  <p>Accessing a value in a Hash requires using its key:</p>

  <p>puts grades[â€œJane Doeâ€] # =&gt; 0</p>
</blockquote>

